[2
Date: 23 Aug 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 23 Aug 2001 [edited

Foot and mouth disease spreads in Zimbabwe
------------------------------
The outbreak of foot and mouth disease (FMD) has spread to 5 properties in
Masvingo, Matabeleland North and South provinces of Zimbabwe, bringing to 6
the number of feedlots infected by the disease over the past 5 days. A task
force, including director of veterinary services Stuart Hargreaves and a
senior official from the Veterinary Services Council, has been set up to
monitor the situation and control the spread of the disease.
The outbreak has been described as a national crisis requiring concerted
efforts to control it. The veterinary officials have so far inspected 100
properties involving 100 000 cattle in the 3 provinces and are optimistic
about containing the disease.
To date, 5 further properties have been positively identified on clinical
signs and quarantined. All cattle movements have been suspended until
further notice except for those going directly to slaughter at registered
abattoirs for local consumption. Dairy products have also been suspended
until further notice, Hargreaves said.
